post_text: The NSAA has decided to allow students to carry over their 19-20 physicals into 20-21. This does NOT apply to incoming Freshman. We will not be offering physicals at the school so you will need to make arrangements to get those completed before the start of Fall sports. It is also recommended that those with existing health conditions see their physician for a wellness check. Incoming 6th graders will need a sports physical and incoming 7th graders will still be required to complete a complete school physical. Contact Mrs. Gorwill with questions.

post_text:
Recycling Update:
I have been working with both Keep Keith County Beautiful and Western Resource Group to replace the large white container that was here temporarily for plastics and aluminum. That trailer was only available during the winter as it is placed at Lake McConaughy during the summer. I thought I had a replacement lined up to return with the help of the village board. However, there are currently no containers to replace it and the cost of a large container is expensive. However, WRG recently found an old, used stock trailer that can be used for plastics and aluminum cans, and the cost is much less. If anyone has old stock trailers that you are willing to sell, they are interested in purchasing more. You can call Aaron at 308-284-7353. Since there will now be two trailers to transport to Ogallala, I would also be interested in volunteers to help out. Please comment below if you would be interested. Thanks!

If anyone has old stock trailers that you are willing to sell, they are interested in purchasing more. You can call Aaron at 308-284-7353. Since there will now be two trailers to transport to Ogallala, I would also be interested in volunteers to help out. Please comment below if you would be interested. Thanks!

Due to anticipated Directed Health Measurers in effect due to Covid-19 the committee felt violations may exist if the reunion is held as planned. This was a difficult decision, but in order to comply with all guidelines this was the prudent choice. This decision was made June 1 to postpone for one year until July 24, 2021. Postcards will be sent out now with this information alerting everyone of the new date next summer. This will be your only notification. The plan will be the same. Vendors for the meals with registration beginning at 9:00 a.m. in the park.
Please check out this website http://69121.touchpros.com and mail your donations to help fund this project to Arthur County Schools, PO Box 145, Arthur, NE 69121 in care of Terria Hampton.

It's Teacher Appreciation week, I want to express my appreciation to all of our Teachers for their hard work and dedication to our students and education, especially during this very different time we are experiencing.

I also want to thank our Paras, Substitutes, Bus Drivers, Custodians, Coaches, and our Secretary/Bookkeeper. All are teachers in some small way, all are adapting to our current environment. All of them have an impact on our youth.

Thank you to all of our teachers no matter what role they serve, you are appreciated especially in times like these.

WE ARE BETTER TOGETHER

Sincerely,

Barry Schaeffer, Superintendent/K-6 Principal

post_text: At the beginning of March, the 3rd grade was investigating what seeds need to survive and what types of soils they grow best in. We planted cucumber seeds in Miracle Grow, another brand of potting soil, sand, and a combination of the soils. Later when learning was continued at home some of the cucumber plants were sent home in ice cream buckets with the students to care for. Parents and students have shared their pictures of the developing plants with me, and I believe that most are growing well. Hailey‚Äôs plant has really grown and has produced tendrils that are attempting to grab onto the curtain cords in her window. Eli and Elivia‚Äôs plants have blossoms and tiny cucumbers on them. I thought others might enjoy the pictures that they have shared with me.

Elementary Parents: Because of how quickly the situation developed last week and we had to send students home sooner than we would have liked, there are many personal belongings that were left behind in our Elementary classrooms and lockers.

In order to return the items we have set up a time on Wednesday April 1 from 9 AM - 11 AM to have you come in an get the items. Please also return any packet materials for them to review. They will also be providing new packets for you as we continue with our learning.

Teachers in those classrooms will bag up your child's things and meet you in the parking lot to hand you the bags and exchange packet materials, you will not need to come into the buildings. We will be watching to see you approach. Please contact your teacher to let them know what time you will be there. Again you will not need to come into the building we will meet you at your car.

post_text:
Yearbook, get your yearbooks!

I wish we weren‚Äôt having to do this online, but here we are so let‚Äôs make the best of it! I‚Äôve emailed all 7-12 students about purchasing yearbooks. Yearbooks are $27 or if your child would like their name printed on the cover of the yearbook it is $30. All I need from you right now is your ordering information. The cost will go onto your student‚Äôs school bill. Please email me with how many yearbooks and if you‚Äôd like a name on them by April 3rd. My email is mandy.vasa@arthurcountywolves.org.

Now, help the yearbook staff out! We plan to make a memory out of this experience. Please email me any pictures you are willing to share of your time at home. This doesn‚Äôt just have to be school work, we‚Äôre going to get creative with some candid pages and would appreciate your help!

Feel free to reach out to me with any questions, it doesn‚Äôt even need to be yearbook related=) I miss seeing you all, can‚Äôt wait until we are back in school again!

-Mrs. Vasa

post_text: Jump Rope for Heart Celebration!! The kids did an outstanding job and were able to raise $1,421 this year. As our highest fund raising class, the 3rd graders started the celebration off by taping our kind volunteer Piper, with the help of our 10th graders, to the wall. Successfully I might add! We then recognized our students who were able to raise the most money from all of our elementary classes and presented them with a certificate. Lastly, some of our lucky kids were able to throw a pie in Ms. Sutton‚Äôs face to really celebrate their hard work. Thank you to all of our parents, friends and family, and community members that helped with our fundraiser this year! P.S. It wouldn‚Äôt allow me to post videos as well so they are in the comments!

post_text: Congratulations to the Speech Team on their Third Place Finish at MNAC Speech today! The OID Team of Rayford, Faith, Sheridan, Alex, and Catherine took First Place. Piper and Payton placed Third in Duet Acting, while Faith was First in Poetry. Rebekkah and Gracie placed First in Duet Acting, Emma was Second in Persuasive Speaking, and Payton placed Second in Humorous Prose. Mary placed First in Informative Speaking, Whitley was First in Persuasive Speaking, and Alex received First Place Ballots from Prelims through Finals in Entertainment.

8th Grade Quiz Bowl team won Reserve MNAC Champs out of 14 teams today to claim the silver medals! Undefeated in pool play, we were seeded in the top of the tournament bracket. A win over Sargent got the Wolves to the championship round. In the Championship round against Arnold (a rematch from pool play), Arnold jumped out to a quick lead. The Wolves made a great comeback and tied the score by the 10th round. A tough battle to the end! Great day!

post_text:
Varsity Quiz Bowl are Runner Up MNAC Champs! Ten teams participated in today‚Äôs double elimination tournament.

The Wolves first match against Stapleton ended in a tie-breaker round with our team on top. The second match we won against Arnold. The third match against Anselmo/Merna also ended with a tie-breaker round with A/M coming out on top. The fourth match against Sandhills/Thedford was a win for us!

This brought us to the championship around to play Anselmo/Merna again. We won the first match 30 to 5!!!

Unfortunately, we were Anselmo/Mernas only loss so we had to play them once more for the title.

In our final match, the score was tied by the tenth round. By the twelfth and final round, Anselmo/Merna pulled ahead by 10 for the win.

Great Job, Wolves! üê∫ ü•à

post_text:
The Tooth Tour is coming on March 2. Forms were sent home with the elementary students on Monday. If you could please have your students return those forms tomorrow (Wednesday February 26) So we can scan and email the forms to the WCHD; it will help the the WCHD personnel in planning and providing services that day. We will set them up on the stage at the high school for the day.

For Junior high and high school students forms are available at the high school office or may be downloaded from the announcement on the web page. We need the forms back by Wednesday if at all possible and no later than Thursday. Thank you.

post_text:
We have windchill forecasts for tonight and tomorrow that are well below zero, please make sure your students have the proper winter clothes when they come to school in the morning.

Also, just a reminder of no school on Monday February 17 due to teacher inservice in Hershey and that our K-6 students will not have classes on Wednesday February 19 and Thursday February 20 due to the staff attending the State Reading Conference.
7-12 students will have classes on Wednesday and Thursday and we will run our regular bus routes for those 7-12 students who ride the bus, on those days.

One more reminder we have school on Friday, February 21 for grades K - 12. We will dismiss at 2:40 p.m.

- Barry Schaeffer, Superintendent

All elementary parents! If you have not heard yet, we have started our Kids Heart Challenge today and your kids will be coming home with their welcome packets. A representative was here yesterday to kick things off and we walked through everything today so we are ready to get rolling. The Challenge will run until the 21st and we will have a celebration following the conclusion. Most of the information will be on the welcome packet but If you have any questions at all please let me know. Here is a link to the Arthur County Public homepage and there are some additional challenges online for the kids to enjoy! Thanks for your help!

Ms. Sutton
